-- 
Hungary Government Reserve Decline Accelerates, Napi Reports

-- B y   E d i t h   B a l a z s
-- 
2011-08-26T06:00:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-26/hungary-government-reserve-decline-accelerates-napi-reports.html
Hungary tapped 52 billion forint
($275 million) of the 90 billion forint in reserves set aside in
the 2011 budget in the past three months,  Napi Gazdasag 
reported, citing its own calculations.  The government has mainly used the reserves for capital aid
for unprofitable state airline Malev Zrt. and state-owned
development bank MFB Zrt. and has earmarked 13.4 billion forint
for the state asset manager MNV Zrt. for undisclosed purposes,
according to the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Edith Balazs in Budapest at 
 ebalazs1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  